(Should I tell someone about it?)

15
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:00,080
How did Dai Shiyao get hurt?

16
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:06,440
They said he fought scouts
in Wuyi Alley.

17
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,360
I'm asking you:

18
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:10,840
What's the story behind the stab wound?

19
00:01:12,100 --> 00:01:13,200
He's got exceptional skills.

20
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,960
No one can get close enough to touch him

21
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:17,120
except for you.

22
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:21,160
Right.

23
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,800
I injured him by accident.

24
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:25,360
An accident?

25
00:01:27,070 --> 00:01:29,120
You nearly pierced his whole shoulder.

26
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:31,040
If he were hit by shrapnel

27
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,160
or grazed by bullets,

28
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,720
those can still be called accidents.

29
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,320
But a short blade

30
00:01:35,320 --> 00:01:37,000
was driven straight into his shoulder.

31
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,480
You call that an accident?

32
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,480
That's between me and the Young Marshal.

33
00:01:45,120 --> 00:01:46,320
This is a marital affair.

34
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,640
I owe you no explanation.

35
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,760
I get it now.

36
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:52,440
When there's danger,

37
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:55,240
you hide behind marital affairs.

38
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:57,320
When there's no danger,

39
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,240
you suspect him, hurt him,

40
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:01,840
and play your revenge games.

41
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:05,280
Don't think I don't know
what's on your mind.

42
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:07,400
He's been digging into your case,

43
00:02:08,360 --> 00:02:10,560
staying up all night
at the Police Bureau.

44
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,560
He's done so much for you,

45
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,680
but you

46
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,040
treat him like a murderer.

47
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,960
Do you even have a brain

48
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,800
or any feelings at all?

49
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:24,160
If you've got time to argue with me,

50
00:02:25,440 --> 00:02:26,960
go treat the Young Marshal.

51
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,880
If you hadn't stabbed him,

52
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,920
could a few scouts have hurt him?

53
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,480
I wouldn't have had to treat his wounds.

54
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,760
If anything happens to him,

55
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:37,960
all of Nancheng will be in danger.

56
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,240
Qin Shiyue.

57
00:02:41,320 --> 00:02:43,160
Think this through carefully.

58
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,440
What matters more to you,

59
00:02:46,440 --> 00:02:48,280
your family's honor or Nancheng?

60
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:05,120
What's your name?

61
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,040
Come here.

62
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:12,000
I'll call you Gray.

63
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,640
Madam.

64
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,560
You haven't eaten all night.

65
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:20,560
Have something.

66
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,640
Jinxiu.

67
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,600
Do you think I'm unworthy
of the Young Marshal?

68
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:28,760
Of course not.

69
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,800
From what I see,

70
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,120
